  "content": "to_string()))?;\n\n        // Delete knowledge files for this scope\n        crate::knowledge_files::delete_scope_files(&self.data_dir, scope_id)?;\n\n        info!(\"Deleted {} entries for scope '{scope_id}'\", uuids_to_delete.len());\n        Ok(())\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Step 6: Register module in lib.rs\n\nAdd to `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`:\n\n```rust\npub mod lite_store;\n```\n\n\n### Step 7: Run tests to verify they pass\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- test_lite_store`\nExpected: PASS\n\nIf hnsw_rs API doesn't match exactly, fix the following:\n- Check `Hnsw::new()` — may need different argument order or types\n- Check `hnsw.insert()` — the tuple type `(&Vec<f32>, usize)` vs `(&[f32], usize)`\n- Check `hnsw.search()` — parameter types and `Neighbour` field names\n- Check if `Hnsw` needs a lifetime parameter — if so, use `'static` or `Box::leak` pattern\n- The `file_dump` method signature: `(&Path, &str)` — may need `Path` vs `&Path` adjustment\n",
